similar to lambda in java and python
An arrow function expression (previously, and now incorrectly known as fat arrow function) 
has a shorter syntax compared to function expressions and does not have its own this, arguments, super, or new.target.
Arrow functions are always anonymous(no name).

1.Map : The map() method creates a new array with the results of calling a function for every array element. 

example : get the size of eachelement

var elements = [
	'Hydrogen',
	'Helium',
	'Lithium',
	'Beryllium'    
];
var a2 = elements.map(function(s){ return s.length; });
console.log(a2);

var a3 = elements.map(s => s.length);
console.log(a3);
output :: [8, 6, 7, 9]
output :: [8, 6, 7, 9]


******************************************************************************************************************

filter() 

example : filtering sports whose number of letters is greater than 4.

var sports = [
	"cricket",
	"chess",
	"Tennis",
	"FootBall",
	"ludo"	
]
var newSports = sports.filter(s => s.length > 4);
console.log(newSports);
output :  ["cricket", "chess", "Tennis", "FootBall"]

*************************************************************************************************************

reduce() :
The reduce() method executes a reducer function (that you provide) on each member of the array 
resulting in a single output value.

let group = [2,4,6,8,10];
let sum = group.reduce((x,y) => x + y);
console.log(sum);

output:  30   //sum of all elements


*************************************************************************************************************

map() : array as output
filter() : array as output
reduce() : single output value



